The paper deals with the specification and reasoning of strategic behaviours in multi-agent systems, which falls under the category of logic and artificial intelligence. Specifically, it introduces a quantitative extension of Strategy Logic (SL) and demonstrates its applications in multi-agent systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.FL (Fuzzy Logic), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
